1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:04,937
‎PREVIOUSLY ON <i>‎TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

2
00:00:04,938 --> 00:00:06,739
You didn't do anything wrong.

3
00:00:06,740 --> 00:00:10,376
So why do you
have to think of yourself as trash?

4
00:00:10,377 --> 00:00:11,276
It's frustrating.

5
00:00:11,277 --> 00:00:14,580
Are you still in contact with your family?

6
00:00:14,581 --> 00:00:16,582
<i>We had promised to meet and talk</i>

7
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:19,752
<i>for the first time in a while,
but then that thing with Tomoki happened…</i>

8
00:00:19,753 --> 00:00:22,121
- Say…
- Yukanai!

9
00:00:22,122 --> 00:00:24,223
Please send that to your wife.

10
00:00:24,224 --> 00:00:26,592
<i>Tell her that this is
your current workplace.</i>

11
00:00:26,593 --> 00:00:29,195
<i>Ask her to come and see it sometime.</i>

12
00:00:29,996 --> 00:00:30,897
Sora

13
00:00:31,998 --> 00:00:33,433
hasn't been able to go to school yet.

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,568
I want

15
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:37,537
to talk with Sora.

16
00:00:39,672 --> 00:00:41,073
I have to ask Sora first.

17
00:00:41,074 --> 00:00:42,575
Daddy.

18
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:48,348
Hello.

19
00:00:48,848 --> 00:00:50,750
Daddy, come with me.

20
00:00:52,852 --> 00:00:54,888
- Maybe a little later.
- Hurry, okay?

21
00:00:55,655 --> 00:00:56,489
‎Okay.

22
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:00,659
You make them call you "Daddy"?

23
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:02,595
- No…
- Then why?

24
00:01:03,696 --> 00:01:04,531
Well…

25
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:07,567
I don't know why either.

26
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:12,872
Look at this.

27
00:01:16,109 --> 00:01:17,342
I'll contact you again

28
00:01:17,343 --> 00:01:19,412
after asking Sora whether
he wants to see you or not.

29
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:21,214
Thanks.

30
00:01:21,714 --> 00:01:22,714
Tatsuki!

31
00:01:22,715 --> 00:01:24,616
- Tatsuki, let's play <i>Mario Kart</i>.
- Tatsuki.

32
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:25,517
I'll join later.

33
00:01:25,518 --> 00:01:27,219
- We need an opponent.
- Join us.

34
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:28,387
Okay, I'll be there.

35
00:01:28,388 --> 00:01:30,356
- Hurry.
- I got it.

36
00:01:31,324 --> 00:01:32,192
They're a handful, huh.

37
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:37,330
Kind of.

38
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:39,265
Bye.

39
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:51,678
So… how did it go?

40
00:01:54,647 --> 00:01:56,449
She said she'll tell Sora
that I want to see him.

41
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,619
I'm glad to hear that.

42
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,823
I felt kind of bad,
thinking that maybe I had done something

43
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:05,892
out of line.

44
00:02:06,893 --> 00:02:09,762
Well, I'm glad I got to talk to her.

45
00:02:17,337 --> 00:02:18,937
NATIONAL MATHEMATICS COMPETITION
FINAL QUESTION

46
00:02:18,938 --> 00:02:20,372
Thanks for waiting, Umine.

47
00:02:20,373 --> 00:02:21,241
Sorry.

48
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,077
Daddy, do you know how to solve this?

49
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:26,079
Why am I "Daddy"?

50
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,951
Never mind. What do you need help with?

51
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,820
It's a practice question
for the math competition.

52
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,956
Let's see.

53
00:02:37,524 --> 00:02:38,925
Whoa, this is hard.

54
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:41,027
You're this advanced?

55
00:02:41,794 --> 00:02:43,530
I don't know how to solve this at all.

56
00:02:48,935 --> 00:02:49,769
I think I got it.

57
00:02:56,442 --> 00:02:58,844
Ta-da!

58
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:00,612
Good day.

59
00:03:00,613 --> 00:03:02,247
I'm the witch,

60
00:03:02,248 --> 00:03:04,416
- Riri!
- Hey, Riri.

61
00:03:04,417 --> 00:03:07,019
We have to hurry or we'll be late
for the School of Magic.

62
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:09,121
- Give me one minute.
- Let's fly to school.

63
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:10,622
Riri, you can't!

64
00:03:10,623 --> 00:03:11,591
What?

65
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:14,227
Don't take Daddy away!

66
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:16,296
You call him "Daddy"?

67
00:03:16,896 --> 00:03:19,131
- You're so weird.
- I'm not weird.

68
00:03:19,132 --> 00:03:20,032
Stop.

69
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,901
Forget you.

70
00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:24,170
Umine.

71
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:25,738
Are you okay?

72
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:34,279
- Who wants to vote for the picnic?
- Me!

73
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,249
Raise your hand.

74
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:39,918
You're all good to go now.

75
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:42,754
- Thanks, Ajicchan.
- You're welcome.

76
00:03:42,755 --> 00:03:44,056
- Let's go, Daddy.
- Okay.

77
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,224
Votes for the flea market?

78
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,326
- Me!
- Wow, this many votes?

79
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:49,261
There are so many votes for this.

80
00:03:49,262 --> 00:03:51,898
Don't lower your hands.
Keep your hands up.

81
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:53,399
You voted for the picnic?

82
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,267
Picnics are fun.

83
00:03:55,268 --> 00:03:57,703
Results of the final votes are in.

84
00:03:57,704 --> 00:04:00,707
Saturday's Fun Day is a tie between
the flea market and the picnic.

85
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:02,774
No way!

86
00:04:02,775 --> 00:04:04,576
- What should we do?
- Flea market.

87
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:06,745
Picnic would be so much better.

88
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,113
Let's do both.

89
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:09,114
Wow.

90
00:04:09,115 --> 00:04:10,816
It's a fierce battle.

91
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:13,785
I have lots of clothes to get rid of,
so a flea market would be great!

92
00:04:13,786 --> 00:04:15,554
How about selling
roasted sweet potatoes again?

93
00:04:15,555 --> 00:04:18,524
Nice. Let's make a profit,
and use it for food expenses here.

94
00:04:19,025 --> 00:04:21,093
How will they decide what to do?

95
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:22,794
Should we choose with rock-paper-scissors?

96
00:04:22,795 --> 00:04:24,396
Rock-paper-scissors?

97
00:04:24,397 --> 00:04:26,098
Who will represent each side?

98
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,567
- Good question.
- The rep on my side better win.

99
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:29,435
Hey.

100
00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:31,236
- Hey, Daiya.
- It's Daiya.

101
00:04:31,237 --> 00:04:32,704
Daiya, great timing.

102
00:04:32,705 --> 00:04:35,307
You can help us out.

103
00:04:35,308 --> 00:04:36,441
Daiya.

104
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,143
What should we do on Fun Day?

105
00:04:38,144 --> 00:04:39,444
Picnic or flea market?

106
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:40,779
Which one do you choose?

107
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:41,848
What?

108
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:45,451
Please.

109
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:49,821
Flea market of course.

110
00:04:49,822 --> 00:04:51,790
Hooray!

111
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,059
Yay!

112
00:04:54,894 --> 00:04:56,862
- Bye.
- See you.

113
00:04:56,863 --> 00:04:59,097
- What should we sell at the flea market?
- Umine,

114
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:00,466
be careful on your way back.

115
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,302
See you tomorrow, Daddy.

116
00:05:06,439 --> 00:05:08,240
- Bye.
- Bye.

117
00:05:08,241 --> 00:05:09,075
- Hello.
- Hey.

118
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:11,544
How's it going, Daddy?

119
00:05:14,013 --> 00:05:15,380
Stop that.

120
00:05:15,381 --> 00:05:16,381
WHAT TO DO ON FUN DAY
FLEA MARKET

121
00:05:16,382 --> 00:05:18,116
- Oh, they decided on the flea market?
- Yes.

122
00:05:18,117 --> 00:05:20,853
Please put up any items
you no longer use for sale.

123
00:05:22,055 --> 00:05:24,624
I wonder if anyone would take
the rope we used for tug-of-war?

124
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,925
I highly doubt

125
00:05:26,926 --> 00:05:28,393
anyone would want that rope.

126
00:05:28,394 --> 00:05:30,462
That thing takes up a lot of space.

127
00:05:30,463 --> 00:05:31,664
I bet.

128
00:05:32,832 --> 00:05:34,499
Mr. Tatsuki,

129
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,368
should we contact
Umine and Riri's guardians

130
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:38,538
regarding today's incident?

131
00:05:39,772 --> 00:05:41,073
Yeah, since she got hurt.

132
00:05:41,074 --> 00:05:42,808
They got in a fight?

133
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:43,875
Yeah.

134
00:05:43,876 --> 00:05:47,046
They got into an argument,
fighting over Mr. Tatsuki.

135
00:05:48,281 --> 00:05:50,749
- You're so popular.
- It's not like that.

136
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:54,319
Lately, Umine has been
overly attached to Mr. Tatsuki.

137
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:57,190
Today she was even calling him "Daddy."

138
00:05:58,424 --> 00:06:00,193
I wonder if something happened at home.

139
00:06:00,993 --> 00:06:03,362
Should we put a stop to it
before it becomes a habit?

140
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:06,032
There might be a reason behind it, though.

141
00:06:06,632 --> 00:06:07,600
A reason?

142
00:06:09,902 --> 00:06:12,003
Maybe we should focus
on trying to understand

143
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:14,005
Umine's feelings right now.

144
00:06:14,006 --> 00:06:14,841
Okay.

145
00:06:15,641 --> 00:06:18,277
Tatsuki, there's something
I want you to try out.

146
00:06:19,645 --> 00:06:20,779
Sure.

147
00:06:20,780 --> 00:06:22,749
FUJINAGA

148
00:06:36,262 --> 00:06:37,697
I met your dad yesterday.

149
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:41,901
He said

150
00:06:42,468 --> 00:06:44,237
he wants to talk with you.

151
00:06:46,305 --> 00:06:47,840
He wants to apologize to you.

152
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:51,778
What do you want to do?

153
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,925
I'm very sorry
about what happened yesterday.

154
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:09,895
It's all right. How's her injury?

155
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:11,464
Yes, she's totally fine.

156
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:14,533
More importantly,
what about the other child?

157
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:15,867
She's okay too.

158
00:07:15,868 --> 00:07:17,203
What a relief.

159
00:07:18,037 --> 00:07:20,840
- I apologize for all the trouble.
- No problem.

160
00:07:21,908 --> 00:07:23,109
Wanna go to the atelier?

161
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:25,711
Let's go.

162
00:07:26,712 --> 00:07:27,713
Bye.

163
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:32,385
She was never the type to get into fights.

164
00:07:33,719 --> 00:07:35,320
From your perspective,

165
00:07:35,321 --> 00:07:37,623
have you noticed
any changes with her recently?

166
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:40,893
No, nothing comes to mind.

167
00:07:41,761 --> 00:07:43,295
I see.

168
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,564
We'll make sure to keep an eye on her.

169
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:47,233
Thank you.

170
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:53,973
What are we going to do?

171
00:07:54,674 --> 00:07:55,641
Today,

172
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:57,810
we should have some fun using buttons.

173
00:07:58,377 --> 00:08:00,813
- Buttons?
- Yeah. Look at this.

174
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:02,914
Ta-da.

175
00:08:02,915 --> 00:08:04,115
These are all buttons?

176
00:08:04,116 --> 00:08:05,150
Yup.

177
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,853
Choose the buttons you like
from among these,

178
00:08:07,854 --> 00:08:10,223
and paste them onto the paper.

179
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:13,459
How?

180
00:08:14,427 --> 00:08:15,528
Let's see…

181
00:08:16,195 --> 00:08:19,298
Let's start by picking out a button
that reminds you of yourself,

182
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:22,601
and also the ones that remind you

183
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:25,204
of your family and friends around you.

184
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:28,039
Which one should I choose?

185
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,709
You can choose whatever you want.

186
00:08:45,391 --> 00:08:46,259
I want an example.

187
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:48,361
- An example?
- Yeah.

188
00:08:49,328 --> 00:08:50,730
An example, huh…

189
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:54,233
I wonder if I still have the ones
we made before.

190
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:57,336
How about these

191
00:08:58,104 --> 00:08:59,438
as examples?

192
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:01,507
This is interesting.

193
00:09:02,308 --> 00:09:03,609
It is, isn't it?

194
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:10,683
It comes in a lot of different sizes.

195
00:09:12,618 --> 00:09:14,186
There are all sorts of patterns too.

196
00:09:15,421 --> 00:09:16,255
This one is cute.

197
00:09:16,989 --> 00:09:17,890
Yeah, it's cute.

198
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,560
Keep choosing whichever one you like.

199
00:09:22,495 --> 00:09:24,230
I'll choose these for myself.

200
00:09:25,197 --> 00:09:26,566
They remind you of yourself?

201
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:29,901
Nice.

202
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:32,872
Then how about the buttons
for the people around you?

203
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:37,810
Let's see…

204
00:09:40,513 --> 00:09:41,547
This reminds me of Daddy.

205
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:43,616
Yeah.

206
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:12,645
I wonder if this is right.

207
00:10:15,047 --> 00:10:16,449
There’s no right or wrong answer.

208
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,818
Just go with whatever feels right to you.

209
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:23,556
I'm not sure what feels right.

210
00:10:30,363 --> 00:10:33,365
Some buttons are lined up neatly,

211
00:10:33,366 --> 00:10:35,468
and others are kind of scattered.

212
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:40,406
- It's a nice contrast.
- Really?

213
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:20,780
All done.

214
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,281
Very well done.

215
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:30,656
What is it, Riri?

216
00:11:37,263 --> 00:11:38,330
Umine,

217
00:11:39,498 --> 00:11:40,933
I'm sorry about yesterday.

218
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:47,006
I'm sorry too.

219
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:51,510
I'm proud of you guys
for apologizing and making up.

220
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:55,081
Let's play with stuffed animals.

221
00:11:59,085 --> 00:11:59,919
Let's go.

222
00:12:00,853 --> 00:12:01,687
Bye, Daddy.

223
00:12:02,521 --> 00:12:03,788
Bye.

224
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:04,890
Let's go.

225
00:12:06,192 --> 00:12:07,493
Okay then…

226
00:12:28,114 --> 00:12:30,483
It seems like they made up.

227
00:12:31,117 --> 00:12:33,753
Riri had been bottling up
her own stress too.

228
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,387
Is that right?

229
00:12:36,388 --> 00:12:40,391
You know, Umine has been
studying a lot lately, right?

230
00:12:40,392 --> 00:12:42,393
So I think Riri felt a little lonely.

231
00:12:42,394 --> 00:12:45,498
Yeah, Umine is solving
really difficult math problems.

232
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:49,401
Yeah. She's good enough to compete
in the national mathematics competition.

233
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:53,304
It's only natural for her dad
to get fired up.

234
00:12:53,305 --> 00:12:54,839
- This one?
- Yeah.

235
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:57,777
What brought Umine to Yukanai
in the first place?

236
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:00,545
She was way ahead
of her class academically,

237
00:13:00,546 --> 00:13:02,480
which made things awkward
with the other kids,

238
00:13:02,481 --> 00:13:03,649
and so she couldn't fit in.

239
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:07,119
Wow, I've never
heard of such a thing before.

240
00:13:07,686 --> 00:13:08,587
It's interesting, huh?

241
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,294
I brought the rope
to sell at the flea market.

242
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:17,262
Where should I put it?

243
00:13:17,263 --> 00:13:20,098
It would be in the way if you put it here.

244
00:13:20,099 --> 00:13:21,900
Can you leave it in the playroom?

245
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:23,935
- Okay, got it.
- Thank you.

246
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:25,403
Oh no.

247
00:13:25,404 --> 00:13:26,871
Whoa!

248
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:27,772
Are you all right?

249
00:13:27,773 --> 00:13:29,307
I'm all right.

250
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:30,608
YUKANAI

251
00:13:30,609 --> 00:13:34,579
This button here represents Umine herself.

252
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:37,817
The buttons that are lined up neatly,
represent her family.

253
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,954
This button in the center is you, right?

254
00:13:42,955 --> 00:13:44,589
Yes, that seems to be the case.

255
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:47,293
I think the buttons all around
represent everyone at Yukanai.

256
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:50,728
There's quite a contrast between
her home and Yukanai.

257
00:13:50,729 --> 00:13:51,564
Yes.

258
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,535
How was Umine while she was
working on this?

259
00:13:57,136 --> 00:13:58,938
Let's see…

260
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:03,174
I told her to work on it
however she liked.

261
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,478
But she asked to see an example,
and was worried about doing it "right."

262
00:14:08,380 --> 00:14:11,282
Since Umine is good at math,

263
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:14,152
maybe she was looking for
a single, definitive answer.

264
00:14:14,153 --> 00:14:15,820
- That makes sense.
- Yeah.

265
00:14:15,821 --> 00:14:17,822
You might be right.

266
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:18,990
Excuse me.

267
00:14:18,991 --> 00:14:20,491
This is in the way in the playroom,

268
00:14:20,492 --> 00:14:22,160
so can I leave this here?

269
00:14:22,161 --> 00:14:23,428
Sorry, Shi-chan.

270
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:25,830
I don't want that here either.

271
00:14:25,831 --> 00:14:26,831
So, um…

272
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:28,299
It's okay temporarily, right?

273
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,801
- Seriously?
- Sorry.

274
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:30,935
I'll leave it in the corner.

275
00:14:30,936 --> 00:14:32,203
- Right here.
- Sorry.

276
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:34,038
- In this corner.
- Fine.

277
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:36,108
What's the situation with Umine's family?

278
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:39,577
Umine's dad is a single father.

279
00:14:39,578 --> 00:14:42,580
From my conversation with her dad,
I got the impression

280
00:14:42,581 --> 00:14:44,115
that he is kind and proper.

281
00:14:44,116 --> 00:14:46,351
But she's calling Tatsuki "Daddy," right?

282
00:14:46,352 --> 00:14:47,486
Yeah.

283
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:51,156
Is she not getting enough attention
from her dad?

284
00:14:51,757 --> 00:14:54,692
Like, maybe her dad is usually
so busy with work

285
00:14:54,693 --> 00:14:56,762
that they don't get to talk much.

286
00:14:58,597 --> 00:15:02,600
Well, Umine hasn't really reached out
with a call for help just yet,

287
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:04,369
but let's keep a close eye on things.

288
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:05,204
- Okay.
- Okay.

289
00:15:18,217 --> 00:15:20,686
Are you done with your homework?

290
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,388
‎Yeah.

291
00:15:22,488 --> 00:15:25,024
Now I'm thinking about
what to sell at the flea market.

292
00:15:31,697 --> 00:15:32,531
How about this?

293
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,170
You're a big girl now,
so you don't need this, right?

294
00:15:53,018 --> 00:15:55,353
YUKANAI

295
00:15:55,354 --> 00:15:58,122
SATURDAY FUN DAY
YUKANAI FLEA MARKET

296
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:00,059
YUKA-TAMASHI

297
00:16:03,028 --> 00:16:04,829
- What do you want?
- I want a bag.

298
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:05,664
A bag?

299
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:07,332
This is cute. You want it?

300
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,367
- You have so many books.
- We sure do.

301
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:11,269
- Wow.
- All of these are five yen each.

302
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:12,437
That's so cheap.

303
00:16:12,438 --> 00:16:13,504
Want roasted sweet potatoes?

304
00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:14,839
Yes.

305
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,341
- Two please.
- Okay.

306
00:16:16,342 --> 00:16:18,443
Thank you.

307
00:16:18,444 --> 00:16:20,912
Welcome, welcome.

308
00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:22,947
Come one, come all!

309
00:16:22,948 --> 00:16:25,450
Today's featured item is this rope.

310
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:28,486
It's a symbol of unity,
and a token of victory.

311
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:30,254
The undisputed star of the Sports Day.

312
00:16:30,255 --> 00:16:32,523
And would you believe it,
this is only 800 yen.

313
00:16:32,524 --> 00:16:33,858
What would we use that for?

314
00:16:33,859 --> 00:16:35,093
For tug-of-war.

315
00:16:35,094 --> 00:16:37,495
- And when would we ever do that?
- What?

316
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:38,629
- Let's go.
- Hold on.

317
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:39,999
Hey, buy this.

318
00:16:40,966 --> 00:16:42,700
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

319
00:16:42,701 --> 00:16:44,836
- Thank you.
- Come again.

320
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:45,737
- Bye.
- Tatsuki.

321
00:16:45,738 --> 00:16:46,738
Bye.

322
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,540
Hey, if it isn't Rui!

323
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:51,075
- It's really busy.
- Yeah.

324
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:53,544
It's been a while. How've you been?

325
00:16:53,545 --> 00:16:54,546
Okay, I guess.

326
00:16:56,281 --> 00:16:58,049
You have a good eye.

327
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,853
It says "ask" for the price,
but how much is it?

328
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,155
Thank you for asking.

329
00:17:04,022 --> 00:17:05,591
- It's 500 yen.
- That's so cheap.

330
00:17:06,658 --> 00:17:08,026
I want this.

331
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,427
- This?
- Yeah.

332
00:17:09,428 --> 00:17:11,663
- It's cute, isn't it?
- Yeah, it sure is.

333
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:13,532
It's another rabbit.

334
00:17:15,267 --> 00:17:16,667
They can play with it together.

335
00:17:16,668 --> 00:17:17,503
Yeah.

336
00:17:18,137 --> 00:17:19,538
All right, let's see…

337
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:25,611
Umine.

338
00:17:26,278 --> 00:17:27,946
You're really selling that stuffed animal?

339
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:29,715
‎Yeah.

340
00:17:30,482 --> 00:17:31,417
I see.

341
00:17:33,185 --> 00:17:35,821
You used to play with that a lot.

342
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:39,091
But I'm a big girl now.

343
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,460
I see.

344
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,133
Tatsuki.

345
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:51,837
Taking entrance exams is meaningless
unless you ace it.

346
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:02,247
What is it?

347
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,651
I hope you win the math competition.

348
00:18:08,053 --> 00:18:08,887
I'll win a medal.

349
00:18:12,991 --> 00:18:16,328
Shi-chan.

350
00:18:20,632 --> 00:18:22,968
Hello.

351
00:18:24,503 --> 00:18:26,237
That's for high school students.

352
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:29,474
Lately, Umine started working
on high school math too.

353
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:31,477
- What?
- It's still just the basics, though.

354
00:18:32,678 --> 00:18:34,712
- She's already at high school level?
- Yes.

355
00:18:34,713 --> 00:18:37,649
She just keeps solving math problems
all on her own.

356
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,418
That's amazing.

357
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:44,089
Umine, let's play.

358
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:45,724
Let's go to the magical forest.

359
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:48,593
Sorry, I'm working on math right now.

360
00:18:48,594 --> 00:18:50,062
That's too bad.

361
00:18:52,064 --> 00:18:52,898
Then maybe later.

362
00:18:53,832 --> 00:18:54,666
Let's go.

363
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:57,268
Bye. Good luck.

364
00:18:57,269 --> 00:18:58,937
- Let's go.
- Bye.

365
00:18:59,738 --> 00:19:00,639
You don't want to go?

366
00:19:02,608 --> 00:19:04,076
I have to finish all this today.

367
00:19:04,576 --> 00:19:05,544
Really?

368
00:19:06,245 --> 00:19:07,613
You're so studious.

369
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,849
It's the home stretch
before the competition.

370
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:12,184
I see.

371
00:19:24,429 --> 00:19:26,231
I think you miscalculated right here.

372
00:19:27,599 --> 00:19:28,767
‎What?

373
00:19:33,372 --> 00:19:36,308
But you used the correct formula.

374
00:19:38,277 --> 00:19:39,211
Why…?

375
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:40,779
How did this happen?

376
00:19:42,247 --> 00:19:43,849
You'll get it right next time.

377
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,618
It's pointless if it's not perfect.

378
00:19:51,890 --> 00:19:54,693
Umine, it's time for cram school.
Let's get ready to go.

379
00:19:58,797 --> 00:19:59,631
What's this?

380
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:05,837
I'm sorry.

381
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:10,842
Why did you make a mistake?

382
00:20:12,477 --> 00:20:14,947
You want to win the gold medal, right?

383
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:23,088
I'm always telling you
to review your answers, aren't I?

384
00:20:25,824 --> 00:20:26,858
Yes.

385
00:20:30,529 --> 00:20:32,998
We'll be going now.

386
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:43,141
Umine.

387
00:20:44,977 --> 00:20:46,178
See you tomorrow.

388
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,655
<i>When I'm looking at Umine</i>

389
00:20:57,222 --> 00:20:59,224
it reminds me of my own childhood.

390
00:21:00,192 --> 00:21:01,827
Your childhood?

391
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:06,365
When I was around her age,
I was also doing nothing but studying.

392
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:09,835
Um…

393
00:21:12,838 --> 00:21:14,640
I think there's a possibility

394
00:21:15,874 --> 00:21:19,344
that Umine is being subjected
to "tiger parenting."

395
00:21:20,312 --> 00:21:22,546
- Tiger parenting?
- Yes.

396
00:21:22,547 --> 00:21:24,915
For example, making a child study
for a long time

397
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:26,785
and depriving them of playtime,

398
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:30,354
or reprimanding them for mistakes
more than is necessary

399
00:21:30,355 --> 00:21:32,591
would certainly raise such suspicions.

400
00:21:33,158 --> 00:21:35,227
Some parents are focused
on their child's education.

401
00:21:36,094 --> 00:21:39,498
Yes, and that's why it's difficult
to know where to draw the line.

402
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:44,168
Umine is working hard
of her own free will, and I understand

403
00:21:44,169 --> 00:21:46,504
the desire to live up
to your parents' expectations,

404
00:21:46,505 --> 00:21:48,139
because I felt the exact same way.

405
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,974
I also agree

406
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:53,111
that Umine is studying of her own accord.

407
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:54,812
But I also think

408
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:58,516
she's being cornered into thinking that
she has no choice but to push herself

409
00:21:58,517 --> 00:22:00,385
in order to live up to expectations.

410
00:22:03,388 --> 00:22:04,389
There are times

411
00:22:04,956 --> 00:22:06,691
when parents themselves aren't even aware

412
00:22:06,692 --> 00:22:08,593
that they are pressuring their kids.

413
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:10,262
Is that right?

414
00:22:12,097 --> 00:22:13,999
She might be unknowingly
pushing herself too hard

415
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:16,601
and causing her emotional state
to become unstable.

416
00:22:18,603 --> 00:22:23,174
That might also be the reason why

417
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:25,877
she started calling you "Daddy."

418
00:22:29,781 --> 00:22:32,317
Okay, I'll keep a close eye on her.

419
00:22:41,226 --> 00:22:43,462
I'm naming her Usa-chan.

420
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:45,831
Usa-chan.

421
00:22:47,132 --> 00:22:48,600
Usa-chan.

422
00:22:49,434 --> 00:22:50,935
- It's so cute.
- I just made it.

423
00:22:50,936 --> 00:22:53,637
Wow. This part

424
00:22:53,638 --> 00:22:55,339
is so colorful.

425
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,675
Yeah, it's colorful.

426
00:23:03,915 --> 00:23:06,385
She's all dressed up.

427
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:09,121
Look at this.

428
00:23:12,824 --> 00:23:13,825
What's the matter?

429
00:23:16,161 --> 00:23:18,163
It's nothing.

430
00:23:23,335 --> 00:23:24,536
It's okay to quit, you know.

431
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,409
Something got in my eye, that's all.

432
00:23:31,943 --> 00:23:32,844
I'm okay.

433
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:34,478
Let's be friends.

434
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:38,082
- I'm all dressed up. It's cute, right?
- I'm so jealous.

435
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,385
I want to dress up fancy too.

436
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:42,019
Then I'll help you out.

437
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:43,854
Hooray. Thanks.

438
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:45,791
- Come this way.
- I can use this.

439
00:24:00,372 --> 00:24:01,373
<i>Tatsuki,</i>

440
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:03,909
why are you crying?

441
00:24:04,743 --> 00:24:06,745
You can't have dinner
until you finish that.

442
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:08,947
Yes.

443
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,150
Crying

444
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:14,486
isn't going to solve anything, you know.

445
00:24:27,699 --> 00:24:29,901
Wake up. Let's get started.

446
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:32,236
Okay.

447
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:33,137
GRADES

448
00:24:33,138 --> 00:24:34,805
No matter how hard you try,

449
00:24:34,806 --> 00:24:37,609
taking entrance exams is meaningless
unless you ace it.

450
00:24:40,111 --> 00:24:44,216
If you want to be a person of value,
produce results.

451
00:25:01,032 --> 00:25:03,200
YUKANAI

452
00:25:03,201 --> 00:25:05,102
Do it in 30 seconds.

453
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:06,170
Make it 30 seconds.

454
00:25:06,171 --> 00:25:08,072
I can do it in 20 seconds.

455
00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:10,742
- Really, 20 seconds?
- I can do 17 seconds.

456
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:17,215
Are you sleeping well at night?

457
00:25:19,584 --> 00:25:20,418
‎Yeah.

458
00:25:20,986 --> 00:25:21,820
When's your bedtime?

459
00:25:24,656 --> 00:25:25,724
Daddy,

460
00:25:26,458 --> 00:25:28,960
my whole life is on the line right now.

461
00:25:29,961 --> 00:25:32,430
This isn't the time to be
sleeping or playing.

462
00:25:33,131 --> 00:25:34,499
I understand that, but…

463
00:25:35,534 --> 00:25:36,668
Daddy,

464
00:25:37,469 --> 00:25:38,570
are you on my side?

465
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:40,405
Of course.

466
00:25:41,006 --> 00:25:41,840
Then

467
00:25:42,674 --> 00:25:43,708
please stay quiet.

468
00:25:53,184 --> 00:25:56,655
What made you come to like math?

469
00:26:04,095 --> 00:26:05,930
I guess it's because

470
00:26:05,931 --> 00:26:08,466
it was the thing I was best at
among all my lessons.

471
00:26:12,103 --> 00:26:13,872
Even though I get scolded if I mess up.

472
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:16,608
By your dad?

473
00:26:22,747 --> 00:26:24,549
How does he scold you?

474
00:26:30,388 --> 00:26:31,723
He tells me,

475
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:33,892
"No dinner until you get it right."

476
00:26:36,695 --> 00:26:38,096
Then you'll get hungry, right?

477
00:26:40,565 --> 00:26:43,568
But it's my own fault
for not being able to solve it.

478
00:26:47,138 --> 00:26:48,974
Sometimes you just want
to have fun, right?

479
00:26:50,609 --> 00:26:52,510
But I have to get good grades…

480
00:26:56,481 --> 00:26:57,983
Otherwise, even you

481
00:26:58,917 --> 00:27:00,418
will start to hate me.

482
00:27:01,252 --> 00:27:04,122
Don't say things like that.
I will never hate you.

483
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:06,558
Really?

484
00:27:07,325 --> 00:27:08,193
Yes.

485
00:27:09,594 --> 00:27:13,064
You have every right
to think more about yourself.

486
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,968
About myself?

487
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:21,306
Tatsuki, let's play <i>Mario Kart</i>.

488
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:22,674
Let's play.

489
00:27:23,408 --> 00:27:24,976
No, don't go!

490
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:29,513
- Ask Soya--
- Listen here, Umine!

491
00:27:29,514 --> 00:27:32,384
Tatsuki isn't yours to hog, you know.

492
00:27:33,118 --> 00:27:34,952
‎-Let's go.
‎-No!

493
00:27:34,953 --> 00:27:36,553
- Don't take him!
- Stop.

494
00:27:36,554 --> 00:27:37,922
- What?
- Okay, that's enough.

495
00:27:41,092 --> 00:27:42,060
‎Sorry.

496
00:27:50,368 --> 00:27:54,005
Umine, it's almost time
for your cram school.

497
00:27:55,707 --> 00:27:56,941
It's already that time, huh?

498
00:27:59,978 --> 00:28:01,146
Daddy.

499
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:03,048
What is it?

500
00:28:06,317 --> 00:28:07,318
Daddy,

501
00:28:08,386 --> 00:28:11,322
you'll always stay by my side
no matter what, right?

502
00:28:16,561 --> 00:28:20,465
If you have any problems at home,
you can contact me.

503
00:28:24,569 --> 00:28:26,471
TATSUKI

504
00:28:39,317 --> 00:28:40,718
I'M AWAKE
YOU'RE STILL AWAKE?

505
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:42,220
<i>You're still awake?</i>

506
00:28:43,354 --> 00:28:45,623
<i>Yeah, because I'm not finished yet.</i>

507
00:28:49,994 --> 00:28:51,896
<i>Don't push yourself too hard.</i>

508
00:28:55,166 --> 00:28:58,269
<i>Dad says now is the time
to really buckle down.</i>

509
00:29:02,474 --> 00:29:04,476
<i>Did you eat?</i>

510
00:29:06,311 --> 00:29:07,846
<i>My stomach hurts.</i>

511
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:18,356
<i>You really need to get some proper rest.</i>

512
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:30,935
<i>If I don't win a medal, Dad will be sad.</i>

513
00:29:38,243 --> 00:29:39,644
<i>You're doing it for your dad?</i>

514
00:29:40,645 --> 00:29:42,781
<i>What is it
that you really want to do, Umine?</i>

515
00:29:51,222 --> 00:29:52,090
Umine.

516
00:29:53,925 --> 00:29:54,993
Coming.

517
00:29:59,564 --> 00:30:01,099
<i>Dad is calling me.</i>

518
00:30:15,446 --> 00:30:16,747
Ms. Shizuku.

519
00:30:16,748 --> 00:30:18,715
Good morning.

520
00:30:18,716 --> 00:30:21,986
You're up early.
Usually you're still asleep at this time.

521
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,722
About Umine…

522
00:30:25,356 --> 00:30:26,191
Yes?

523
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:28,793
I was thinking it might be a good idea

524
00:30:29,294 --> 00:30:31,362
to have her dad come here once
so we can talk.

525
00:30:32,197 --> 00:30:34,332
Talk about what?

526
00:30:34,899 --> 00:30:36,701
Regarding his approach
to Umine's education.

527
00:30:37,869 --> 00:30:39,636
I was thinking that maybe we should

528
00:30:39,637 --> 00:30:41,573
have a discussion to see
if his current approach

529
00:30:42,073 --> 00:30:43,675
is truly in her best interests.

530
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:48,445
If she's really being subjected
to tiger parenting,

531
00:30:48,446 --> 00:30:51,149
I would certainly
want to do something to address it.

532
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:55,053
But this is a really
difficult issue, isn't it?

533
00:30:56,387 --> 00:30:57,222
What do you mean?

534
00:30:58,223 --> 00:31:00,991
At this stage, what we can do

535
00:31:00,992 --> 00:31:02,493
is kind of limited.

536
00:31:04,128 --> 00:31:06,297
You want to leave this alone
and do nothing?

537
00:31:07,899 --> 00:31:10,033
You're the one who's always saying

538
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:12,769
that we shouldn't meddle
in family matters.

539
00:31:12,770 --> 00:31:14,472
You don't care what happens to Umine?

540
00:31:15,473 --> 00:31:17,675
- That's not what I mean.
- Never mind.

541
00:31:18,610 --> 00:31:19,743
I'll handle it myself.

542
00:31:19,744 --> 00:31:21,311
What are you going to do?

543
00:31:21,312 --> 00:31:23,013
I'll take Umine away from her dad.

544
00:31:23,014 --> 00:31:25,883
- You can't do that!
- What if it all becomes too late?

545
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,751
- Like I said--
- Hey, let's calm down.

546
00:31:27,752 --> 00:31:29,854
You guys are fighting
first thing in the morning?

547
00:31:31,422 --> 00:31:32,624
I'm sorry.

548
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:37,395
I baked some financiers.
Do you guys want some?

549
00:31:38,363 --> 00:31:39,197
Here you go.

550
00:31:39,764 --> 00:31:41,965
Enjoy. One for you too.

551
00:31:41,966 --> 00:31:44,902
Nobody can stay angry
while they're eating something sweet.

552
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:46,503
Come on, eat up.

553
00:31:46,504 --> 00:31:48,273
Whenever you get angry, eat a financier.

554
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:49,741
Got it?

555
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:51,276
Okay.

556
00:31:57,715 --> 00:31:59,283
As for the flea market the other day,

557
00:31:59,284 --> 00:32:01,652
the final accounting
ended up turning a profit,

558
00:32:01,653 --> 00:32:02,953
albeit just barely.

559
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:05,389
- I knew we could count on you.
- Good job.

560
00:32:05,390 --> 00:32:08,326
Although the rope ended up not selling.

561
00:32:10,295 --> 00:32:11,362
Where's Tatsuki?

562
00:32:12,063 --> 00:32:14,332
He's been on his phone for a while now.

563
00:32:14,899 --> 00:32:17,935
I think he's messaging with Umine.

564
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:19,037
With Umine?

565
00:32:20,138 --> 00:32:21,571
It’s not really appropriate

566
00:32:21,572 --> 00:32:24,274
to communicate personally
outside of Yukanai,

567
00:32:24,275 --> 00:32:25,410
right?

568
00:32:26,311 --> 00:32:27,812
Yeah, I don't recommend it.

569
00:32:28,713 --> 00:32:31,648
He’s completely preoccupied with Umine,
as if he's really her daddy.

570
00:32:31,649 --> 00:32:33,150
Yes.

571
00:32:33,151 --> 00:32:37,388
When I mentioned
the possibility of tiger parenting,

572
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:41,092
he became even more involved
with her situation.

573
00:32:41,659 --> 00:32:43,027
I see.

574
00:32:51,536 --> 00:32:52,837
Hey there.

575
00:32:54,038 --> 00:32:56,039
- Oh, the meeting…
- No worries.

576
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,241
It ended already.

577
00:32:58,343 --> 00:32:59,177
I'm sorry.

578
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:03,848
You look like

579
00:33:05,483 --> 00:33:06,751
you're under a lot of pressure.

580
00:33:08,353 --> 00:33:09,187
Really?

581
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:13,758
Tatsuki, why don't you give
button art a try too?

582
00:33:14,325 --> 00:33:15,460
Me?

583
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,260
Um… why?

584
00:33:17,261 --> 00:33:18,896
Let's just do it.

585
00:33:19,964 --> 00:33:24,067
After all, you're also
a subject of my research.

586
00:33:24,068 --> 00:33:26,004
Sit down.

587
00:33:27,772 --> 00:33:30,141
I wonder what they're doing.

588
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:34,645
Maybe it's art therapy.

589
00:33:36,247 --> 00:33:39,017
Professor Mikumo
is taking it upon himself to handle it?

590
00:33:39,717 --> 00:33:40,785
It's kind of rare.

591
00:33:41,786 --> 00:33:42,620
Yeah.

592
00:34:19,590 --> 00:34:21,993
How about something like this?

593
00:34:24,195 --> 00:34:25,763
How did you feel while making this?

594
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:29,634
Nothing in particular.

595
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:36,574
It looked as though you were making it
with hesitation and uncertainty.

596
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:39,877
You may be right.

597
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:43,881
I, myself, wasn't even sure
what I was trying to make.

598
00:34:44,816 --> 00:34:46,117
I see.

599
00:34:48,319 --> 00:34:52,256
Lately, Umine has been relying on you
rather excessively, hasn't she?

600
00:34:53,224 --> 00:34:54,058
Yes.

601
00:34:59,397 --> 00:35:00,565
That’s…

602
00:35:04,001 --> 00:35:05,870
called "transference."

603
00:35:06,537 --> 00:35:09,539
Maybe she's unconsciously
projecting feelings

604
00:35:09,540 --> 00:35:11,509
she'd normally harbor toward her own dad,
onto you?

605
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:14,946
That might be it.

606
00:35:16,214 --> 00:35:18,415
What concerns me even more, however,

607
00:35:18,416 --> 00:35:20,451
is the fact that right now

608
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:22,253
you are…

609
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:30,361
experiencing countertransference.

610
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:34,232
COUNTERTRANSFERENCE

611
00:35:35,199 --> 00:35:36,400
Countertransference?

612
00:35:37,768 --> 00:35:39,637
Without even realizing it,

613
00:35:40,872 --> 00:35:42,507
you've become way too invested in her.

614
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:47,612
When I see Umine,

615
00:35:48,346 --> 00:35:52,316
I'm reminded of myself when I was a child.
So I feel the need to do something.

616
00:35:53,351 --> 00:35:56,420
I understand how you feel,
but you should step back a little.

617
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:00,857
Why?

618
00:36:00,858 --> 00:36:04,227
Exchanging messages with her
until this late,

619
00:36:04,228 --> 00:36:06,464
is really going a little too far.

620
00:36:07,198 --> 00:36:09,099
Then who is going
to look after her instead?

621
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:11,501
- Who'll listen to her cries for help?
- Calm down.

622
00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:12,769
I am calm.

623
00:36:12,770 --> 00:36:14,238
Pull yourself together.

624
00:36:17,875 --> 00:36:19,744
If you lose your head over this,

625
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:21,946
you won't be able to save her.

626
00:36:24,415 --> 00:36:25,750
I know that.

627
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:35,226
Take some time off work.

628
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:40,498
I can't do that…

629
00:36:41,399 --> 00:36:43,167
This is a corporate mandate.

630
00:37:16,434 --> 00:37:18,836
I told him to take time off work
for a while.

631
00:37:20,671 --> 00:37:21,839
I see.

632
00:37:22,607 --> 00:37:25,309
But he doesn't really have
anywhere else to go, does he?

633
00:37:26,644 --> 00:37:27,978
Oh, right.

634
00:37:27,979 --> 00:37:29,280
I forgot he lives here.

635
00:37:30,681 --> 00:37:33,150
I'm sure he'll come back.

636
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:36,520
You guys can go home now.

637
00:37:37,355 --> 00:37:38,355
Okay.

638
00:37:38,356 --> 00:37:39,856
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

639
00:37:39,857 --> 00:37:42,026
- Thank you.
- Bye.

640
00:38:03,047 --> 00:38:06,217
ANDO

641
00:38:21,532 --> 00:38:22,533
Sora,

642
00:38:23,434 --> 00:38:24,335
what's the matter?

643
00:38:29,340 --> 00:38:30,708
I'll meet with him.

644
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:36,714
With your dad?

645
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:40,418
I don't care either way.

646
00:38:58,069 --> 00:38:59,769
UMINE

647
00:38:59,770 --> 00:39:02,406
<i>Daddy, I'm tired.</i>

648
00:39:10,848 --> 00:39:11,882
I'm tired.

649
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:14,985
It's just a little bit more.

650
00:39:15,753 --> 00:39:17,722
Finish that, and you can go to sleep.

651
00:39:18,956 --> 00:39:19,790
Yes.

652
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:38,275
<i>You don't have to work hard
just to get praised by your dad.</i>

653
00:39:39,243 --> 00:39:41,812
<i>Just do whatever you enjoy.</i>

654
00:39:53,190 --> 00:39:57,928
YU
CAN YOU MAKE TIME TO MEET TOMORROW?

655
00:40:05,403 --> 00:40:06,469
Just a little more!

656
00:40:06,470 --> 00:40:08,204
- Just a little more!
- It's almost done.

657
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:09,472
All right,

658
00:40:09,473 --> 00:40:11,207
it's done.

659
00:40:11,208 --> 00:40:12,876
There you go.

660
00:40:12,877 --> 00:40:14,644
- I want to go next.
- Be careful.

661
00:40:14,645 --> 00:40:16,346
- I'm going next.
- No, it's me.

662
00:40:16,347 --> 00:40:18,948
- Take turns, everyone.
- Keep climbing up.

663
00:40:18,949 --> 00:40:20,483
Go for it.

664
00:40:20,484 --> 00:40:21,785
- Are you okay?
- You can do it.

665
00:40:21,786 --> 00:40:24,854
- Good job.
- You did it.

666
00:40:24,855 --> 00:40:27,691
The rope you couldn't sell
has a new life now.

667
00:40:29,660 --> 00:40:31,495
I'm glad it found a new home.

668
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:33,963
Nice. Good job.

669
00:40:33,964 --> 00:40:36,733
Good job.

670
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:38,334
- You can do it.
- Have you seen Tatsuki?

671
00:40:38,335 --> 00:40:40,737
No, not yet.

672
00:40:40,738 --> 00:40:41,939
You can do it.

673
00:40:42,573 --> 00:40:44,107
I see.

674
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:44,942
- Go for it.
- Okay.

675
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:58,355
Welcome.

676
00:41:12,036 --> 00:41:13,270
It's been a while.

677
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:18,476
He's working
at an alternative school right now.

678
00:41:19,009 --> 00:41:20,411
I went to visit the other day.

679
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:24,648
There are all kinds of kids,
and sometimes it gets tough

680
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:26,650
but I'm managing somehow.

681
00:41:28,352 --> 00:41:29,620
Excuse me.

682
00:41:35,359 --> 00:41:36,660
Please enjoy.

683
00:41:40,564 --> 00:41:41,565
How about you, Sora?

684
00:41:42,867 --> 00:41:44,168
How have things been lately?

685
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:58,015
I feel terrible
about what I did to you, Sora.

686
00:42:00,484 --> 00:42:02,052
I acted selfishly,

687
00:42:02,553 --> 00:42:04,488
without ever stopping
to consider your feelings.

688
00:42:06,156 --> 00:42:07,925
I should've been right there by your side,

689
00:42:08,425 --> 00:42:10,227
as the one who understood you best.

690
00:42:12,463 --> 00:42:15,299
Instead, all I did was hurt you.

691
00:42:24,775 --> 00:42:25,976
I'm really sorry.

692
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:37,688
So?

693
00:42:43,327 --> 00:42:46,330
Must be nice for you,
having a new job and all,

694
00:42:48,399 --> 00:42:50,634
but I haven't even been able
to go back to school.

695
00:42:54,104 --> 00:42:55,506
Even if you can't go to school,

696
00:42:56,273 --> 00:42:59,376
- I'll support whatever you want to do--
- Shut up.

697
00:43:03,213 --> 00:43:05,049
Everything is all over now.

698
00:43:07,051 --> 00:43:08,452
All thanks to you.

699
00:43:15,659 --> 00:43:17,561
YUKANAI

700
00:43:21,966 --> 00:43:24,735
Answer that. It's your work, right?

701
00:43:33,677 --> 00:43:34,612
Excuse me.

702
00:43:43,420 --> 00:43:45,356
- Hello?
<i>- Mr. Tatsuki.</i>

703
00:43:46,323 --> 00:43:47,324
Um…

704
00:43:48,792 --> 00:43:49,959
Umine

705
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:53,430
is in the atelier
and she's refusing to come out.

706
00:43:55,032 --> 00:43:57,433
<i>She told us to call you over right now.</i>

707
00:43:57,434 --> 00:44:00,204
I told her
that you're on leave for a while.

708
00:44:01,305 --> 00:44:04,107
Then she said, "But he promised

709
00:44:04,108 --> 00:44:06,543
that he’d always
stay by my side no matter what."

710
00:44:08,145 --> 00:44:09,113
Okay.

711
00:44:09,613 --> 00:44:10,981
I'll call you back.

712
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:29,500
Sorry, I have to go.

713
00:44:38,842 --> 00:44:40,511
You didn't used to be like this.

714
00:44:42,146 --> 00:44:43,013
What?

715
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:48,886
You never helped me when I needed it.

716
00:45:08,372 --> 00:45:10,173
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

717
00:45:10,174 --> 00:45:11,742
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
